  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-DOC-04, add a 2-button view toggle group to the command bar (`AppsList20Regular` = list / `Grid20Regular` = card), active = `appearance="primary"`, inactive = `appearance="subtle"`. Implement **List view** as the default, with columns: Selection checkbox · Pin (icon visible only on pinned rows; click toggles) · Name (file icon + link-styled) · Modified · Modified by (avatar + name) · Match · Three-dot menu. Headers sortable (toggle asc/desc with `ArrowSortUp/Down` indicator). **Default sort: `modifiedAt DESC`** — requires FR-BFF-01 (`modifiedAt` + `modifiedBy` projection from task 050). Card view keeps the existing `ResultCard` rendering with 3-dot menu replacing inline icons (from task 040). Pinned rows always sort to top regardless of active column sort. View preference persists in localStorage keyed by `(userId, matterId)`. Selection state persists across view toggles. Pin state survives reload.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior frontend developer expert in Fluent UI v9 `DataGrid`/`Table`, React 16/17 hooks (`useState`, `useMemo`, `useEffect`), and the Semantic Search PCF state architecture. Familiar with localStorage scoping patterns and ADR-022 React platform constraints.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SemanticSearchControl.tsx` exposes `view`, `sortColumn`, `sortDirection`, `selection`, `pinnedIds` state. NEW `ListView.tsx` component renders the column grid with sortable headers, selection checkboxes, and pin icon. NEW `SortableColumns.tsx` component encapsulates sort-indicator + click-to-toggle header behavior. Default sort `modifiedAt DESC`. localStorage keys: `spaarke.docs.view.{userId}.{matterId}`, `spaarke.docs.pinned.{userId}.{matterId}`. PCF builds clean. Code-review + adr-check pass.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-DOC-04 introduces the list view that holds the column-header row + selection checkboxes required by FR-DOC-02 (bulk-action bar). Default sort `modifiedAt DESC` depends on FR-BFF-01 (task 050) projecting `modifiedAt`/`modifiedBy` into `/api/ai/search` results — without those, the list cannot render the Modified column. Pin state is per-user-per-matter localStorage only (no Dataverse write, per spec) and pinned rows sort above all others regardless of active column sort. Card view continues to use the existing `ResultCard.tsx` rendering, augmented by the 3-dot menu from task 040.
    </background>
