  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Command bar shows 2-button view toggle: list (`AppsList20Regular`) + card (`Grid20Regular`); active button uses `appearance="primary"`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">List view default sort is `modifiedAt DESC`; clicking a sortable column header toggles asc/desc with arrow indicator.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">List view columns render in spec order: Selection · Pin · Name · Modified · Modified by · Match · Three-dot menu.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Pinned rows render at the top regardless of active column sort.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Pin icon renders ONLY on pinned rows; clicking the pin column toggles pinned state and persists to localStorage.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">View preference persists across reload, keyed by `(userId, matterId)`; switching matters yields independent preference.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Toggling list ↔ card re-renders without re-fetching data; selection state retained across toggles.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">PCF builds clean; zero hardcoded hex/rgb in touched files.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">axe WCAG 2.1 AA zero violations in light AND dark themes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` skills pass with no unresolved findings.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TASK-INDEX.md shows task 041 as ✅ completed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="View toggle persists per matter">
      <steps>
        <step>Load Matter A, switch to list view, reload — verify list view restored.</step>
        <step>Load Matter B (new matter for this user) — verify default (list) view.</step>
        <step>Switch Matter B to card view, reload — verify card view restored; Matter A preference unaffected.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Preference scoped per `(userId, matterId)`.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Default sort modifiedAt DESC + column sort toggles">
      <steps>
        <step>Open list view — verify rows ordered by `modifiedAt` newest first.</step>
        <step>Click Name column header — verify alphabetical asc, then click again — verify desc.</step>
        <step>Click Modified column header — verify asc, then desc.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Sort state visually indicated; rows re-ordered correctly.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Pinned rows sort to top">
      <steps>
        <step>In list view sorted by Name asc, pin a row that would normally appear in the middle.</step>
        <step>Verify pinned row jumps to top; remaining rows retain Name asc.</step>
        <step>Unpin — verify row returns to its sorted position.</step>
        <step>Reload — verify pin state survives.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Pin state persisted via localStorage; pinned rows always at top.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Selection persists across view toggle">
      <steps>
        <step>In list view, select 3 rows via checkboxes.</step>
        <step>Toggle to card view, then back to list view.</step>
        <step>Verify the same 3 rows are still selected.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Selection state retained in memory across view changes.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Dark mode compliance (ADR-021)">
      <steps>
        <step>Toggle dark mode.</step>
        <step>Verify column headers, sort indicators, checkboxes, pin icons, avatar/name cell use v9 dark tokens.</step>
        <step>Run axe-core in both themes.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Zero WCAG violations; all colors via Fluent v9 semantic tokens.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    Depends on task 040 (3-dot menu provides the `DocumentRowMenu` consumed in the list view row) and task 050 (`modifiedAt`/`modifiedBy` projection from BFF). Selection state is in-memory only for v1 (Owner Clarifications — selection across view toggles required, but not across page reloads). The 2-column header layout consumed by FR-DOC-02 (bulk-action bar, task 045) is enabled here — the bulk bar sits above the column-header row of the list view.
  </notes>

